<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={2000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 5039.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20" /> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.2002748597205</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={2000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{5039}={2000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{5039}}{{2000}}={e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{5039}}{{2000}}\right)}}}={0.22}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{5039}}{{2000}}\right)}}}}{{0.22}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={4.2002748597205}</m></p>
</solution>
